<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4635804>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 11. Weltneria cf. hirsuta collected from Charonia lampas collected in Kwelera Bay. Scanning electron microscopy of external features, female. A—Row of teeth on opercular bar, with nodules; B—Comb collar; C—Opercular area, upper-lateral view showing opercular bars; D—Posterior processes of opercular bars; E—Multifid scales; F—Surface below opercular area showing bifid teeth and spines. Abbreviations: ob—opercular bar, obp—posterior process of opercular bar." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4635804/files/figure.png" .

